==English==

===Noun===
'''semantic memory'''

#A subcategory of [[declarative memory]], semantic memory stores general information such as names and facts.
#A system of the brain where logical concepts relating to the outside world are stored.
#:''Directions to mom’s house are stored in your '''semantic memory'''.''
#(Advertising) the memory system which stores information relating to [[brand|brands]], thus where brand positioning is established.
#:''Product information that helps you decide which brand of soda to drink and why is stored in your '''semantic memory'''.''

